  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nIn iOS, after the device successfully scans a valid QR code, the device tries to discover the other device (sender) in the network. The user will get a permission dialog to allow finding devices in their local network, which is **automatically** requested by the iOS. \r\n\r\nThe user needs to accept the permission for a successful pairing. If not, the pairing process is blocked in iOS.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/19339952/f82fc4e3-ae72-4780-b21a-a093b1a7c44b\" width=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) Open Status\r\n2) Tap on \"Sign in\"\r\n3) Scan a sync QR code\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status Version: nightly [31/05] \r\n- Operating System: iOS\r\n\r\n### Notes:\r\n\r\n- Starting from iOS 14, we need the user’s permission to discover devices in the user’s local network. https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2020/10110/\r\n\r\n- This issue is reproducible only in PR/nightly/release builds. We can NOT reproduce this in debug build as this permission is requested when debug build is first opened in the mobile/simulator to load the bundle from the metro bundler.\r\n\r\n- Unfortunately, this permission type is yet to be added to the permission library we use on mobile due to the unavailability of explicit permission APIs from [Apple](https://developer.apple.com/forums/thread/663888). We need to create some helper functions to check if required.  We need a design, something like requesting camera permission before scanning the QR, to ensure smooth and successful pairing.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
